---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Terms of Service | OrizPDF"
	description="Terms of service for OrizPDF — free, browser-based PDF tools."
	canonical="/terms"
>
	<section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 to-blue-50/30 border-b border-gray-200/60">
		<div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
			<h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 tracking-tight mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
			<p class="text-gray-600">Last updated: March 27, 2026</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 prose prose-gray max-w-none">
		<h2>Acceptance of Terms</h2>
		<p>By accessing and using OrizPDF, you accept and agree to be bound by these terms. If you do not agree, please do not use our services.</p>

		<h2>Service Description</h2>
		<p>OrizPDF provides free, browser-based PDF tools that allow users to merge, split, compress, convert, and edit PDF documents. All processing occurs locally in your web browser.</p>

		<h2>Use of Service</h2>
		<p>You may use OrizPDF for both personal and commercial purposes, subject to these terms:</p>
		<ul>
			<li>You must not use the service for illegal purposes</li>
			<li>You must not attempt to reverse-engineer or exploit the service</li>
			<li>You are responsible for the content you process using our tools</li>
			<li>You must not use automated scripts to overload the service</li>
		</ul>

		<h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
		<p>OrizPDF's website, design, and original code are open source under the MIT license. The PDF processing libraries we use (pdf-lib, pdfjs-dist, etc.) are subject to their own licenses.</p>

		<h2>Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
		<p>OrizPDF is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind. We do not guarantee that the service will be error-free, uninterrupted, or produce specific results.</p>

		<h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
		<p>In no event shall OrizPDF be liable for any damages arising from the use or inability to use our tools. Since all processing happens in your browser, we have no access to your files and cannot be held responsible for any data loss.</p>

		<h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
		<p>The AI Summarizer feature integrates with Puter.js, which is subject to <a href="https://puter.com/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Puter's terms of service</a>.</p>

		<h2>Changes to Terms</h2>
		<p>We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.</p>

		<h2>Contact</h2>
		<p>Questions about these terms? Contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@pdf.oriz.in">legal@pdf.oriz.in</a>.</p>
	</article>
</BaseLayout>
